(thunder rumbling softly)

04:37.360 --> 04:38.736
(sighs)

04:40.571 --> 04:41.781
(thunder rumbling)

04:46.828 --> 04:48.538
{\an5}FLIGHT ATTENDANT:
At this time,
on behalf of the crew

04:48.621 --> 04:50.415
{\an5}of Flight 1015 from
Washington, D.C., to Tel Aviv,

04:50.498 --> 04:52.709
{\an5}we'd like to welcome you
on board and invite you

04:52.792 --> 04:54.544
{\an5}to take the safety information
card out of the seat pocket

04:54.627 --> 04:56.170
{\an5}in front of you,
and follow along

04:56.254 --> 04:59.090
{\an5}as we perform
our safety demonstration.

04:59.173 --> 05:01.551
{\an5}FLIGHT ATTENDANT:
As we prepare for takeoff,

05:01.634 --> 05:03.386
we would like to remind you

05:03.469 --> 05:05.722
{\an5}to please remain in your seats
until the captain has turned off

05:05.805 --> 05:07.724
the "fasten seat belt" sign,

05:07.807 --> 05:10.935
{\an5}indicating then that it is safe
to move about the cabin.

05:11.019 --> 05:14.731
{\an5}To get us on our way,
make sure your seat is up,

05:14.814 --> 05:16.190
{\an5}all electronic devices
are put away,

05:16.274 --> 05:18.735
and your tray table is stowed.

05:18.818 --> 05:21.029
{\an5}All exits on this airplane
are clearly marked.

05:21.112 --> 05:22.613
{\an3}Excuse me.

05:22.697 --> 05:24.574
{\an5}Take a moment to locate
the nearest one.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.409
{\an5}Keep in mind,
it may be behind you.

05:26.492 --> 05:28.911
If you have a carry-on,

05:28.995 --> 05:31.205
{\an5}push it all the way
under the seat in front of you.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.590
{\an5}(eerie music playing
over headphones)

05:40.673 --> 05:42.592
{\an5}MALE NARRATOR (over headphones):
Chapter one:

05:42.675 --> 05:46.637
{\an5}"The Mystery of
Northern Gold Star Flight 1015."

05:46.721 --> 05:48.264
The passengers were buckled up,

05:48.347 --> 05:51.100
{\an5}and the safety demonstration
had started.

05:51.184 --> 05:54.645
{\an5}It was already raining outside
at Dulles International Airport,

05:54.729 --> 05:58.399
{\an5}and a large thunderstorm
was brewing over the Atlantic.

05:58.483 --> 06:01.319
{\an5}Little did the passengers
of Flight 1015 know,

06:01.402 --> 06:03.279
in less than an hour,

06:03.362 --> 06:06.657
{\an5}their plane would disappear
from flight control radar,

06:06.741 --> 06:08.910
never to be heard from again.

06:08.993 --> 06:09.702
Oh, my God.

06:09.786 --> 06:11.788
(thunder crashes,
engine roaring)

06:17.627 --> 06:19.921
{\an5}I'm Rodman Edwards,
the host of <i> Enigmatique,</i>

06:20.004 --> 06:22.006
{\an5}and I'm going to
lead you through

06:22.090 --> 06:24.258
the last moments of Flight 1015.

06:24.342 --> 06:27.720
{\an5}(whispering):
Past is past.
Past is past.

06:27.804 --> 06:29.806
